SIMPLE: screamer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Screamer
<hw>Scream"er</hw> <pr>(skr⟦emac⟧m"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of three species of South American birds
constituting the family <fam>Anhimidae</fam>, and the suborder
<ord>Palamedeae</ord>. They have two spines on each wing, and the head
is either crested or horned. They are easily tamed, and then serve as
guardians for other poultry. The crested screamers, or chajas, belong to
the genus <gen>Chauna</gen>. The horned screamer, or kamichi, is
<spn>Palamedea cornuta</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something so remarkable as to provoke a scream, as
of joy.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An exclamation mark.</def> <mark>[Printer's
Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Screaming</ent>⟦br⟧
